				\begin{document}$$d=1$$\end{document} for, dgmin=60\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\hbox {dg}_{\hbox {min}}=60$$\end{document}, dgmax=3000\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\hbox {dg}_{\hbox {max}}=3000$$\end{document}.
Step 4 Generate the population of DG sizes randomly using equation
population=(dgmax-dgmin)×rand()+dgmin\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
